########### INSTRUCTIOSNS TO COMPUTE THE HELMHOLTZ SOLID FREE ENERGY OF NAPHTHALENE ############## 

##################################################################################################
(1) Equiliriate the naphthalene crystal (to obtain the reference structure to be used in the extended Einstein crystal at the given T and p)

cd ./npt_crystal_equilibration
"submit.sh" --> submit script
"pamameter.dat" --> a list of pressure and temperature parameters read by "submit.sh"
"npt.sh" --> script read by "submit.sh" to edit input files accordinging to "pamameter.dat"
"IFile_npt" --> directory with all the input files
"director_npt_example" --> the example simulation results

read "submit.sh" first for detailed instructions 
##################################################################################################

##################################################################################################
(2) Apply the extended Einstein crystal method

cd ./extended_Einstein_crytal_method
Copy the final equilibrated configuration from (1) as the initial structure for all the simulations in (2) 
(i.e. the reference structure)

A_solid is the absolute Helmholtz free energy
A_solid = A0 + ΔA0 + ΔA1 + ΔA2 + ΔA_symmetry (see methodology descrption)
ΔA1 = ΔA1_charge + ΔA1_vdwl --> the electrostatic (charge) and van der Waals (vdwl) contributions to ΔA1
ΔA_symmetry --> analytic contribution to A_solid from the molecular symmetry (check molecular point group)

cd ./A0_EA1 --> directory where we calculate A0 for Einstein Arrangement (EA) 1 (see methodology descrption for explaining Einstein Arrangement)
cd ./delta_A0_EA1 --> directory where we compute ΔA0 for EA 1
cd ./delta_A1_charge_EA1 --> directory where we compute ΔA1_electrostatic for EA 1
cd ./delta_A1_vdwl_EA1 --> directory where we compute ΔA1_vdwl for EA 1
cd ./delta_A2_EA1 --> directory where we compute ΔA2 for EA 1
###############################

(a)-(e):
###############################
(a) 
cd ./A0_EA1
"A0_Kmax2500.f" --> example Fortran code to compute A0 for Kmax=4221.640615 kT/Å^2=2500 kcalmol-1/Å^2 for u=Kmax(r-r0)^2 
or kmax=5000 kcalmol-1/Å^2 for u=0.5*kmax(r-r0)^2
(i.e. 0.5*kmax = Kmax and 0.5*k=K)

(Both kmax and Kmax are used in this work because:
for "fix spring/self" in LAMMPS, the spring energy is u=0.5*kmax*r^2
###############################

###############################
(b)
cd ./delta_A0_EA1
"submit_A0_EA1.sh" --> submit script
"k.dat" --> a list of parameters read by "submit_A0_EA1.sh" 
"energies.sh" --> script read by "submit_A0_EA1.sh" to edit input files accordinging to "k.dat"
"energies_re.sh" --> script read by "submit_A0_EA1.sh" to edit input files accordinging to "k.dat"
"IFile_A0" --> directory with all the input files
"director_A0_EA1_example" --> the example simulation results (read "Data_Analyse.sh" first)

read "submit_A0_EA1.sh" for detailed instructions
###############################

###############################
(c)
cd ./delta_A1_charge_EA1
"submit_A1_charge_EA1.sh" --> submit script 
"k_TI.dat" --> a list of paramters for the electrostatic interactions
"energies_A1_charge_EA1.sh" script read by "submit_A1_charge_EA1.sh" to edit input files accordinging to "k_TI.dat"
"IFile_A1_charge_EA1" --> directory with all the input files
"director_A1_charge_EA1_example" --> the example simulation results (read "Data_Analyse.sh" first)

read "submit_A1_charge_EA1.sh" first for detailed instructions
###############################

###############################
(d)
cd ./delta_A1_vdwl_EA1
"submit_A1_vdwl_EA1.sh" --> submit script 
"k_TI.dat" --> a list of paramters for the Lennard-Jones (LJ) van der Waals (vdwl) interactions
"energies_A1_vdwl_EA1.sh" script read by "submit_A1_vdwl_EA1.sh" to edit input files accordinging to "k_TI.dat"
"IFile_A1_vdwl_EA1" --> directory with all the input files
"director_A1_vdwl_EA1_example" --> the example simulation results (read "Data_Analyse.sh" first)

read "submit_A1_vdwl_EA1.sh" first for detailed instructions
###############################

###############################
(e)
cd ./delta_A2_EA1 
"submit_A2_EA1.sh" --> submit script 
"k_2.dat" --> a list of paramters "num k kmax" read by "submit_A2_EA1.sh"
"energies.sh" --> script read by "submit_A2_EA1.sh" to edit input files accordinging to "k.dat"
"energies_re.sh" --> script read by "submit_A2_EA1.sh" to edit input files accordinging to "k.dat" for continuing simulations
"IFile_A2" --> directory with all the input files
"director_A2_EA1_example" --> the example simulation results (read "Data_Analyse.sh" first)

read "submit_A2_EA1.sh" first for detailed instructions
##################################################################################################

##################################################################################################
References:
#############For the description of the original Einstien crystal method, see:
1.D. Frenkel and B. Smith, Understanding Molecular Simulations, 2nd ed. (Academic, London, 2002).
2.D. Frenkel and A. J. Ladd, J. Chem. Phys. 81, 3188 (1984).
New Monte Carlo Method to Compute the Free Energy of Arbitrary Solids. Application to the Fcc and Hcp Phases of Hard Spheres
3.E. J. Meijer, D. Frenkel, R. A. LeSar and A. J. C. Ladd, J. Chem. Phys. 92, 7570 (1990)
Location of Melting Point at 300 K of Nitrogen by Monte Carlo Simulation

#############For the usage of symbols and the fortran code in "A0_EA1" for the extended Einstein crystal method, see:
4.J. L. Aragones, C. Valeriani, and C. Vega, J. Chem. Phys. 137, 146101 (2012).
Note: Free Energy Calculations for Atomic Solids through the Einstein Crystal/molecule Methodology Using GROMACS and LAMMPS
5.C. Vega, E. Sanz, J. L. F. Abascal, and E. G. Noya, J. Phys.: Condens. Matter 20, 153101 (2008).
Determination of Phase Diagrams via Computer Simulation: Methodology and Applications to Water, Electrolytes and Proteins

#############For the OPLS-AA and SPC force field paramters, see:
6.W. L. Jorgensen, D. S. Maxwell, and J. Tirado-Rives, J. Am. Chem. Soc. 118, 11225 (1996).
Development and Testing of the OPLS All-Atom Force Field on Conformational Energetics and Properties of Organic Liquids
7.H. J. C. Berendsen, J. P. M. Postma, W. F. van Gunsteren, and J. Hermans, In Intermolecular Forces, edited by B. Pullman (Reidel, Dordrecht, 1981), p. 331.
